---
import { Button } from "@bibleio/design";
import Layout from "~/layouts/Layout.astro";

import User from "~/components/icons/User.astro";
import { MainSection } from "@bibleio/design";
---

<Layout title="Home">
  <section
    id="landing"
    class="border-stroke relative flex h-screen flex-col items-center justify-center overflow-clip border-b p-32"
  >
    <div
      class="flex h-full w-full max-w-[100rem] flex-col justify-center gap-48"
    >
      <h1
        class="motion-preset-slide-up-sm text-text-solid pt-72 text-left text-[128px] leading-none max-[1400px]:text-[96px] max-[530px]:text-[48px]"
      >
        Give your rights for the gospel
      </h1>
      <h3
        class="motion-preset-fade-lg text-h3 text-text max-[1000px]:text-body leading-[150%]"
      >
        Do you create Christian resources? Jesus calls us to freely give them.
      </h3>
    </div>
    <div class="absolute left-0 top-0 -z-50 h-full w-full">
      <div
        class="motion-preset-fade-lg animate-spin-slow bg-yellow absolute left-1/2 top-[-50%] h-[49vw] w-[40vw] rounded-full blur-[15vmin]"
      >
      </div>
      <div
        class="motion-preset-fade-lg animate-spin-slow bg-green absolute bottom-[-15%] right-[-20%] h-[49vw] w-[45vw] rounded-full blur-[15vmin]"
      >
      </div>
      <div
        class="motion-preset-fade-lg animate-spin-slow bg-purple absolute bottom-[-50%] left-[20%] h-[49vw] w-[40vw] rounded-full blur-[15vmin]"
      >
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <MainSection>
    <div
      class="flex w-full items-center justify-center gap-24 overflow-hidden px-32 py-32"
    >
      <h1 class="text-h1 text-text leading-none">What, why?</h1>
    </div>

    <div id="why" class="grid grid-cols-2 grid-rows-2 max-[800px]:grid-cols-1">
      <div
        class="border-stroke relative flex flex-col gap-24 overflow-clip border-b border-r p-48 max-[580px]:p-24"
      >
        <h2 class="text-h2 text-text leading-none">Why freely give?</h2>
        <p class="text-body text-text leading-[220%]">
          Jesus says in Mat 10:8, <span class="text-body text-accent-reversed"
            >“Freely you received; freely give.”</span
          > We freely receive so much, including our own salvation, so Jesus calls
          us to freely give too. The rest of the Bible never tells us we should commercialize
          ministry or restrict it (2 Cor 2:17), it tells us the opposite (1 Peter
          5:2). Jesus freely gives his gift of salvation, Paul always freely gave
          (1 Cor 9:18), and the Bible warns against serving money so many times (Luk
          16:13).
        </p>
      </div>
      <div
        class="border-stroke relative flex flex-col gap-24 overflow-clip border-b p-48 max-[580px]:p-24"
      >
        <h2 class="text-h2 text-text leading-none">The problem</h2>
        <p class="text-body text-text leading-[220%]">
          Paywalls and copyright affect how the gospel can be spread. So many
          Christian resources have paywalls or copyright restrictions, including
          some huge popular Bible translations, books, devotionals, songs, all
          restricted under copyright or paywalls, so either you have to pay, or
          get restricted permission to worship and spread the gospel, and if you
          can’t, too bad.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div
        class="border-stroke relative flex flex-col gap-24 overflow-clip border-r p-48 max-[580px]:p-24"
      >
        <h2 class="text-h2 text-text leading-none">More problems</h2><ul
          class="list-disc"
        >
          <li class="text-body text-text leading-[220%]">
            The Bible (popular translations or niche language translations)
            belong to a group of big companies who heavily restrict its use
          </li>
          <li class="text-body text-text leading-[220%]">
            While most of the world has a Bible translation, less than half of
            the world has one they can legally share
          </li>
          <li class="text-body text-text leading-[220%]">
            Other languages cannot translate popular copyrighted English
            resources
          </li>
          <li class="text-body text-text leading-[220%]">
            Churches cannot sing to God without paying music royalties or
            getting permission first
          </li>
          <li class="text-body text-text leading-[220%]">
            Lot’s of popular authors, pastors, and organizations put a paywall
            or copyright on their Christian resources
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-body text-text leading-[220%]">
          And this sucks, especially for digital intellectual property (like a
          Bible translation, or book), where freely giving it would cost nothing
          to the organization or person, yet most resources are still
          copyrighted/paid.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div
        class="border-stroke relative flex flex-col gap-24 overflow-clip p-48 max-[580px]:p-24"
      >
        <h2 class="text-h2 text-text leading-none">
          Paywalls block potential users
        </h2>
        <p class="text-body text-text leading-[220%]">
          Christian resources are meant to benefit God's kingdom, so we should
          freely give it to the entire kingdom of God, and consider other
          methods of funding or publishing.
        </p>
        <div
          class="rounded-16 border-stroke bg-fg-1 backdrop-blur-popup grid grid-cols-2 gap-16 border p-24 max-[480px]:p-8"
        >
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-12">
